Scientific Name: Sorghum bicolor x Sorghum bicolor var. Sudanense
Notes: Environmental Tolerances: Does very poorly under low-N conditions like most grasses.
Soil Drainage: ["Somewhat poorly drained","Moderately well drained","Well drained","Excessively drained","Well drained muck"]
Notes: Weeds: Mature, frost-killed plants become quite woody
Notes: Excellent forage; not as winterhardy as other perennial forage grasses but establishes quickly so may still be useful as a cover crop.
